        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued July 25 at 2:35PM PDT until July 25 at 3:00PM PDT by NWS Reno NV</headline>
        <description>SVRREV

The National Weather Service in Reno has issued a

* Severe Thunderstorm Warning for...
Plumas County in northern California...
Sierra County in northern California...

* Until 300 PM PDT.

* At 235 PM PDT, a severe thunderstorm was located over Whitehawk, or
near Blairsden, moving east at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Quarter size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Damage to vehicles is expected.

* Locations impacted include...
Blairsden, Beckwourth, Graeagle, Iron Horse, Delleker, Valley
Ranch, Whitehawk, Clio, Calpine, Sattley, C-Road, Mohawk Vista,
Lake Davis, Portola, Ca 89 At Sierra-Plumas Co Line, and
Beckwourth-Nervino Airport.
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
